In [[mathematics]], '''modular units''' are certain units of [[ring (mathematics)|rings]] of integers of fields of [[modular function]]s, introduced by {{harvs|txt|last=Kubert|authorlink=Daniel Kubert|last2=Lang|author2-link=Serge Lang|year=1975}}.  They are functions whose [[zero of a function|zeroes]] and [[pole (complex analysis)|poles]] are confined to the cusps (images of infinity).

